parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of problems, including stalling, loss of power, and fire hazards, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Intermittent headlight failure
dead battery
power door locks inoperable
manual release mechanism inoperative
electrical features dying
horn malfunction
erratic radio operation
dome lights staying on
vehicle security system activating for no reason
and power door locks not opening electrically.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Turn Signal and Hazard Switch Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning turn signals and hazard switches can cause confusion on the road, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Right turn signal becoming inoperative
all bulbs lighting up except for the right side marker light
marker light and other lights flashing with the 4-way flashers
and hazard switch interfering with turn signal operation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Battery and wiring harness problems can cause electrical system failures, leading to stalling, loss of power, and fire hazards.
symptoms: Battery dying
wiring harness catching fire
chafing and shorting
and battery cable shifting forward and drooping onto the idler arm.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning horn can cause safety issues, as it may not be audible in emergency situations.
symptoms: Horn being too hard to press
dealer unable to fix the problem
and horn system needing to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning doors and locks can cause safety issues, as occupants may be trapped inside the vehicle.
symptoms: Doors not opening electrically
manual release mechanism inoperative
and doors not warning occupants when ajar.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to vibrate, lose power, or become stuck in gear, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates
the transfer case clutch is defective
the vehicle rolls when on an incline
the service AWD light comes on
the vehicle will not shift into gear
the vehicle shimmies
and there is vibration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, become stuck in gear, or suddenly accelerate, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The transmission goes out
the reverse and overdrive gears fail
the vehicle will not shift into gear
the vehicle suddenly accelerates
and the vehicle pulls to the right.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front hubs can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The front hubs need to be replaced frequently
with some owners experiencing failure at around 20
000 miles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sun gear can cause the vehicle to lose power, become stuck in gear, or suddenly accelerate, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The sun gear goes out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can cause accidents or near-misses, as other drivers may not be aware that the vehicle is braking or stopping.
symptoms: The brake lights do not function
the hazard flashers do not work
the turn signals are malfunctioning
the brake light switch has failed
the multi-function switch is loose or faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the multi-function switch can cause the turn signals, hazard flashers, and brake lights to malfunction, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The turn signals do not work
the hazard flashers do not work
the brake lights do not function
the multi-function switch is loose or faulty
the windshield wipers come on when making a right turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake lights do not function
the hazard flashers do not work
the turn signals are malfunctioning
the fog lights vibrate excessively
the fiberclass cover on the front bumper assembly does not fit properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball joints can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience a clunking noise
vibration
or a sudden loss of control while driving
especially when turning or braking. The ball joint may break
causing the tire to fall off or the vehicle to collapse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Front end problems can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience a clunking noise
vibration
or a sudden loss of control while driving
especially when turning or braking. The front end may collapse
causing the tire to bend inward or outward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience a vibration
noise
or a sudden loss of control while driving
especially when turning or braking. The suspension system may need an overhaul
including replacement of bearings and pins.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Deceptive business practices can lead to financial losses and frustration for consumers.
symptoms: The dealership may misrepresent the condition of the vehicle
fail to disclose known defects
or refuse to repair problems under warranty. Consumers may experience multiple problems with the vehicle
and the dealership may not take responsibility for fixing them.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission mount cross member can cause the transmission to break loose, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Loud noise coming from the muffler
transmission mount cross member is rotten and ready to break loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter element can cause rattling noises, decreased engine performance, and potentially lead to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: Rattling noise coming from the exhaust system
broken catalytic converter element.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil cooler hose can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially resulting in engine failure or fire.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the front of the engine
oil cooler hose (P/N 15194578 pipe and 15194579 hose) leaking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine stalling on long trips
vehicle stalling multiple times during a single trip.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oxygen sensor can cause decreased engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: Bad oxygen sensor
multiple occasions of oxygen sensor failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dome override switch can cause electrical system malfunctions, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Lights staying on
personal alarm going off frequently
dome override switch causing electrical issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heating system can cause discomfort, distraction, and potentially lead to hypothermia or other health issues.
symptoms: Little or no heat
thermostat replacement
system flushing
and heated seats providing some relief.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of power can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle losing power while driving at any speed
losing power when turning corners
and then starting again.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft sensor can cause engine stalling, decreased engine performance, and potentially lead to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: Vehicle cranking but not starting
hesitation on acceleration
crankshaft sensor replaced according to TSB.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The oil leak can cause engine damage, overheating, and potentially result in engine failure or fire.
symptoms: Oil leak
concern about possible vehicle fire due to oil leak.
